        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2824476345" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1970241541125723273">Entertaining and beautifullly written, quite true to the legend, but...:<br/>1. Like the other volumes, there is no climax. There is suspense, yes, but a mild one.<br/>2. Not often, but disturbing enough, Mary Stewart`s feminist (and inaccurate) ideas harm the story: the women`s treachery is justified, „normal” (because they are opressed!), while men are beasts, ready to forgive their children`s murderer if they are paid for their loss. <br/>Sad, could have been the best Arthurian Saga, the author being a real</span>
  <span id="freeText1970241541125723273" style="display:none">Entertaining and beautifullly written, quite true to the legend, but...:<br />1. Like the other volumes, there is no climax. There is suspense, yes, but a mild one.<br />2. Not often, but disturbing enough, Mary Stewart`s feminist (and inaccurate) ideas harm the story: the women`s treachery is justified, „normal” (because they are opressed!), while men are beasts, ready to forgive their children`s murderer if they are paid for their loss. <br />Sad, could have been the best Arthurian Saga, the author being a real talent.</span>
